snippet.textDisplay:
funny to see such a fuss and i seriously doubt that people who are getting into arguments have some serious misconception.

This master piece from Abbas Ali Khan is no doubt an exception. 

Very powerful lyrics. As this track is all about debate between " Ishq-e- Haqiqi"  ( Love for creator Allah) & " Ishq-e-Majazi" (Love for creation).

lets take a line from this track..." Mai gada nahee Main faqeer hoon" .....Word " Gada" refers to that person who goes door to door and beg from people. But "Faqeer" is a person who opts to live a very basic and limited life and who's total focus is to get closer to the creator and he only asks Allah for his requirements. Ad no interest in material things.

So a very friendly advice to all pals that please first try to improve  your urdu skills before getting into any arguments and i believe that you all are from good families. Please avoid vulgarity as it only gives a bad impression.
